 BE command [parameters]
    or
 BE filespec

   Enhance Batch files with sound  (BEEP),  color  (SA),  keyboard
input  (ASK),  screen  addressing   (ROWCOL),   character   output
(PRINTCHAR, BOX, WINDOW), and other attributes (CLS and DELAY).

 Available Commands
     ASK       BEEP         BOX        CLS         DELAY
     GOTO      PRINTCHAR    ROWCOL     SA          WINDOW

 BE menufile
   Execute multiple BE commands from the file, 'menufile'.

 BE ASK ?
   Get help on using the ASK command.
==================================================================

 CALIBRAT [d:] [switches]

   Optimizes the speed and reliability of  data  transfer  to  and
from your hard disk.

   Switches
 /BATCH       Skip all prompts and exit to DOS when done
 /BLANK       Blank the screen while performing pattern tests
 /NOCOPY      Don't copy the current track being tested
 /NOFORMAT    Only perform pattern testing, not formatting
 /NOSEEK      Don't perform the seek tests
 /PATTERN:n   Perform pattern testing at level 'n'
 /R:file      Generate a report and send the result to 'file'
 /RA:file     Generate a report and Append it to 'file'
 /X:d         Exclude drives from testing (ie. /X:def)
==============================================================

 Disk Editor
 DISKEDIT [d:] [path] [file] [switches]

   View and edit the entire contents of a diskette or  hard  disk,
including disks that DOS cannot recognize  or  access.  Repair  or
rescue damaged files or their data.

   Switches
 /M   Maintenance mode - bypass DOS and examine disk directly
 /X:d Exclude drive(s) from absolute sector processing
==============================================================

 Disk Monitor
 DISKMON [switches]

   Has three main features: prevents data from  being  written  to
your disk without your approval; displays name of  drive currently
being accessed in upper right corner of screen;  parks  hard  disk
heads.

   Switches
 /STATUS    On-screen status summary
 /PROTECT+  Turn protect features on
 /LIGHT+    Turn DiskLight feature on
 /PARK      Park disk drive heads
 /UNINSTALL Remove DISKMON from memory
==============================================================

 DISKREET [switches]

   Encrypts (scrambles)  and  passwordprotects  files.  Creates  a
passwordprotected "virtual" disk drive  on  which  all  files  are
encrypted.

   Switches
 /CLOSE                 Close all NDisks
 /DECRYPT:filename      Decrypt specified file
 /ENCRYPT:filename      Encrypt specified file
 /HIDE[:drive letter]   Hide an NDisk
 /OFF
 /ON
 /PASSWORD:xxxxxx       Set password to xxxxxx
 /SHOW[:drive letter]   Show an NDisk
==============================================================

 Disk Tools
 DISKTOOL

   A set of six utilities that allow you to make  disks  bootable,
recover from the DOS RECOVER command, revive  defective diskettes,
mark clusters, and create or restore data rescue diskettes.
==============================================================

 FILEFIND [filespec] [search-text] [switches]

   Locates misplaced files by searching for their  data  or  names
through  all  available  drives  (including  network  drives)  and
directories. Changes file attributes.

 FileSpec - examples
   *.*            Search entire current drive
   .\*.*          Search current directory
   *:*.*          Search all drives
 Switches
   /S             Include files in subdirectories
   /C             Search current directory
   /CS            Case sensitive search
   /A[+/=]        Set/Reset Archive Bit
   /R[+/=]        Set/Reset Read-only Bit
   /HID[+/=]      Set/Reset Hidden Bit
   /SYS[+/=]      Set/Reset System Bit
   /CLEAR         Clear (remove) all file attributes
   /D[mm-dd-yy]   Set the date to [month-day-year]
   /T[hh:mm:ss]   Set the time to [hour:minute:second]
   /NOW           Set the date and time to current date and time
   /TARGET:dl     Tests if files will fit on target drive 'dl'
   /O:file        Save the list to 'file'
   /BATCH         Automatically exit program
==============================================================

 FILEFIX [filename]

   Diagnoses and repairs damaged Lotus 1=2=3, Symphony,  and dBASE
files. UnZaps dBASE files.
==============================================================

 FILESAVE [switches]

   Protects deleted  files  from  being  overwritten  immediately;
helps ensure recovery of deleted data.

   Switches
 /STATUS    Display FileSave status
 /ON        Enable FileSave
 /OFF       Disable FileSave
 /UNINSTALL Remove FileSave from memory
==============================================================

 IMAGE [d:][d:]... [switches]

   Ensures that accidentally formatted disks can be  recovered  by
creating  a  "snapshot"  record   of   their   vital   bookkeeping
information.

   Switches
 /NOBACK  Do not create the backup image file IMAGE.BAK
==============================================================

 Norton Cache
 NCACHE-F [switches]     (Fast)
   or
 NCACHE-S [switches]     (Small)

   Uses some of your computer's RAM as a  holding  area  for  data
from your disks;  this improves performance  by making frequently-
needed data faster to access. Can also be used to buffer data that
is to be written to your disk.

   Switches
 DOS=n         Size in DOS memory
 EXT=n         Size in Extended Memory
 EXP=n         Size in Expanded Memory
 BLOCK=n       Cache Block Size
 USEHIDOS=Y/N  Use high DOS memory
 USEHMA=Y/N    Use XMS HMA

 DELAY=ss.hh   Delay for Write-Thru
 INI=fspec     Configure filespec
 QUICK=ON/OFF  Return Prompt Quickly

 PAUSE         Pause display scrolling
 PRINT         Send display to printer
 HELP          Display help screen
 STAT          Display Status Data
 [=]A          Activate/Deactivate caching
 [=]C          Enable/Disable more data
 [=]I          Enable/Disable IntelliWrite
 [=]W          Enable/Disable Write-Thru
 [=]S          Enable/Disable SmartReads
 R=n           Limit Sector Read-Ahead
 G=n           Limit Group Sector Read
==============================================================

 Norton Control Center
 NCC [filename] [/SET]
     or
 NCC [stopwatch switches]
     or
 NCC [quick switches]

   Controls your PC's hardware settings. You may set  cursor size,
change DOS colors, set palette colors, select video  mode,  change
keyboard settings, set mouse speed, and more.

Stopwatch Switches
    /START:n    Start stopwatch number n (range 1=4, default 1)
    /STOP:n     Stop stopwatch number n (range 1=4, default 1)
    /N          No display of current time and date
    /L          Print current time and date on Left side
    /C:comment  Display 'comment'

Quick Switches
    /FAST       Set keyboard to fastest speed
    /BW80       Set display mode to Black and White, 25 x 80
    /CO80       Set display mode to Color, 25 x 80
    /nn         Set the number of lines for EGA or VGA
                   For EGA, nn can be 25, 35, or 43
                   For VGA, nn can be 25, 40, or 50
==============================================================

 Norton Change Directory
 NCD [directory_name] [switches]

   Navigates through and manages the directory structure  on  your
disk, no matter how  complex.  Renames  and  deletes  directories.
Switches to  any  directory,  no  matter  how  deep,  with  a  few
keystrokes.

   Switches
 /R  Rescan disk directory
 /N  Do not write or update TREEINFO.NCD
==============================================================

 Norton Disk Doctor II
 NDD [d:][d:]... [switches]

   Automatically detects and corrects physical  and  logical  disk
errors.

   Switches
 /COMPLETE  Test System and Data Areas
 /FORMAT    Format physically bad track
 /QUICK     Just test System Area
 /R:file    Write a report to 'file'
 /RA:file   Append a report to 'file'
 /REBUILD   Rebuilds an entire disk that has been destroyed
 /UNDELETE  Undelete a DOS partition that was previouly skipped
 /X:d       Exclude drive from testing
==============================================================

 Norton Integrator
 NORTON [switches]

   Allow interactive Norton Utilities call.

   Switches
 /BW      Forces the use of the Black and White color set
 /LCD     For laptop displays. Forces the use of the LCD color set
 /G0      Disable font redefinitions and graphic mouse (EGA/VGA)
 /G1      Disable the graphic mouse (EGA/VGA)
 /NOZOOM  Disables dialog box zooming
==============================================================

 Safe Format
 SFORMAT [d:] [switches]

   Safely formats  a  disk.  Does  not  overwrite  data,  to  make
recovery easier.

   Switches
 /A        Automatic mode; useful in batch files
 /B        Leave space for system files
 /D        DOS Format (same as DOS)
 /N:n      Number of sectors per track (8, 9, 15, or 18)
 /Q        Quick Format
 /S        Copy DOS system files to the disk
 /T:n      Number of tracks (40 or 80)
 /V:label  Place a volume label on the disk
 /size     Size of diskette (ie, /720 will create 720K)
 /1        Format for single-sided use
 /4        Format a 360K diskette in a 1.2M drive
 /8        Format 8 sectors per track
==============================================================

 Speed Disk
 SPEEDISK [d:] [switches]

   Optimizes your hard disk by  reorganizing  the  layout  of  all
files and directories on the disk; also  consolidates  free  space
and defragments files.

   Switches
 /C        Complete disk optimization
 /D        Optimize Directories only
 /U        Unfragment files only
 /Q        Unfragment free space (fill unused gaps)
 /SN[=]    Sort files by Name
 /SE[=]    Sort files by Extension
 /SD[=]    Sort files by Date
 /SS[=]    Sort files by Size
 /V        Turn Read-after-Write Verify ON
 /B        Reboot computer after optimization
 /B  Reboot after optimization
 /C  Optimize complete disk
 /D  Optimize directories only
 /Q  Compress free space only
==============================================================

 System Information
 SYSINFO [switches]

   Reports on all facets of your computer system: hardware, memory
use, networks, available disks, TSRs and device drivers, and more.
Provides benchmarks and performance ratings.

   Switches
 /AUTO:n  Automatic mode, 'n' sec./screen
 /DEMO    Demonstration mode:  unattended  Scrolling  only through
 	  the System Information Benchmark Screens
 /SUMMARY Causes SysInfo to print the same information as  SI v4.5
          in a TTY display
 /TSR     Show only active TSRs
 /N       Bypass live memory probe
==============================================================

 UNERASE [FILENAME]

   Searches for and recovers erased (deleted) files. Automatically
recovers intact files; manual mode allows recovery  of  data  from
files that have been partially overwritten or fragmented.
==============================================================

 UNFORMAT [d:]

   Undo an accidental formatting of a hard  disk,  thereby  making
the data accessible again.
   UnFormat can recover from an  accidental  format,  even  if  no
prior system information was saved. A near-perfect recovery can be
achieved if the system information was saved with IMAGE.
==============================================================

 WIPEINFO [d:] [disk switches] [common switches]
   or
 WIPEINFO [filespec] [file switches] [common switches]

   Totally obliterates erased (deleted) data so that it  cannot be
recovered by any means; applies to single files or entire disks.

Disk Switches
    /E    Wipe all Erased and unused data space only

File Switches
    /N    Non-wiping mode; delete files, but don't wipe
    /K    Wipe the slacK space of a file
    /S    Wipe or delete files in subdirectories also

Common Switches
    /Gn   Follow certain government rules for wiping
    /Rn   Repeat wiping n times; default n=1
    /Vn   Wipe value; default n=0
==============================================================
